KwaZulu-Natal paramedics had to carry a patient across a river and washed-away roads to an awaiting ambulance on Wednesday morning. IPSS Medical Rescue said paramedics  responded to a call alerting them to an elderly woman having difficulty breathing in Shakaville in KwaDukuza. “Due to flooded rivers and damage from the  rains, medics had to carry the patient across rivers and washed-away roads to the ambulance. The patient was treated and stabilised by IPSS advanced life support before she was transported to hospital,” IPSS said. The team thanked community members who assisted in ensuring the patient received  medical treatment. TimesLIVE 